fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Another radiocomputer..." says the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Another radiocomputer..." says the lieutenant, watching you circle around the machine. "Just sitting here without anyone in sight."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "This is the Rehm Civic radiocompute..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is the Rehm Civic radiocomputer, model RC5120, equipped with a Feld mainframe and a Rehm-compatible printer.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good morning, Fortress Accident on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good morning, Fortress Accident on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine, this is East-Insulindian Repeater Station 1."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Doesn't it get lonely, sitting ther..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Doesn't it get lonely, sitting there all by herself?

fields.Title: You: ""Doesn't it get lonely, doing this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't it get lonely, doing this job?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Yes. Is that the production schedu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Is that the production schedule?"

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Four months later by an unknown aut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Four months later by an unknown author: "I am the only one left and it's gotten rather damp here. A few other businesses have gone under too. Slipstream switched to making skis and the hairdressers just left, cursing Martinaise. They're right, though, something's seriously wrong with this place. Martinaise, all of it."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Is the lieutenant a little... scare..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is the lieutenant a little... scared? Just now when he looked around.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "This is a *human interface* -- a re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is a *human interface* -- a retired person sitting behind a switchboard somewhere.

fields.Title: Logic: "Password. Of course it would have a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Password. Of course it would have a password. That's why there's a human administrator involved.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "This appears to be some kind of mac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This appears to be some kind of machine with a cube-shaped heart and a wired framework. The keyboard has a rectangular ON/OFF button; a piece of paper still hangs from the printer.

fields.Title: You: "Look inside the compartment."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look inside the compartment.

fields.Title: You: "It didn't need so many concept arti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It didn't need so many concept artists?

fields.Title: You: "[Step away.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Step away.]

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The filament you have would fit per..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The filament you have would fit perfectly inside the compartment.

fields.Title: You: "Tear off the printout."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tear off the printout.

fields.Title: You: "The what?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The what?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "This place was to be the *Valley of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This place was to be the *Valley of the Heads* -- where the heads of all the *headless* constructs could be found. The player would have been able to choose a head for their headless party member, and each head would been voiced on-air by a professional actor.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Definitely not."
fields.Dialogue Text: Definitely not.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The static gets louder, slowly fill..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The static gets louder, slowly filling up the abandoned hall. Until a voice speaks out, crackling and old, cutting into the air...

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good evening, Fortress Accident on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good evening, Fortress Accident on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine, this is East-Insulindian Repeater Station 1."

fields.Title: Shivers: "On an island on the River Esperance..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On an island on the River Esperance, a small woman, all skin and bones, sits in a room filled with audio equipment. Thousands of tiny lights are reflected back from her prescription lenses, like stars in the dark.

fields.Title: You: "Let it go."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let it go.

fields.Title: Half Light: "That sounds bad -- a log-in *attemp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That sounds bad -- a log-in *attempt*. Something a criminal would do.

fields.Title: You: "It's not very convincing, is it?"
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not very convincing, is it?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The dusty radiocomputer sleeps on i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The dusty radiocomputer sleeps on its wired frame, forgotten and unused. Its keyboard has a rectangular ON/OFF button; a piece of paper still hangs from the printer.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Saint-Brune 1147? That's what the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Saint-Brune 1147? That's what the street sign next to the church said...

fields.Title: Logic: "This must be the information Soona..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This must be the information Soona is looking for -- she knows how to make sense of it.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "But on the other hand, their obliga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But on the other hand, their obligations *were* piling up at an inhuman rate -- a rate that could only be amended by Pyrholidon.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Tiles on the cube are still smoulde..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tiles on the cube are still smouldering, casting the framework in a soft glow. Virescent PLAY and PRINT keys shine on the keyboard.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Something's missing -- there's no t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something's missing -- there's no tape in the player.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "What is clear is that one day an un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What is clear is that one day an unidentified numeric anomaly occurred on the East-Insulindian Lintel front, just as the 'Wirrl Untethered' project was being compiled that day.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We have one of these down at the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We have one of these down at the station, but I never really learned how to use it."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: "The voice recites: "I am contractua..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The voice recites: "I am contractually obliged to protect the privacy of the filament holder Fortress Accident. Without filing a warrant with Lintel, I cannot give you access to this filament."

fields.Title: You: ""How do I do that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do I do that?"

fields.Title: You: ""Do you have any other information..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you have any other information about this company?"

fields.Title: You: "Gosh, where did they get all this m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Gosh, where did they get all this money?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Let's just say it was a *real adven..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let's just say it was a *real adventure* for their Igaunijan investor.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The production schedule depicts the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The production schedule depicts their glorious descent into bankruptcy.

fields.Title: You: "This must be the anomaly Soona ment..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This must be the anomaly Soona mentioned in the church log.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "On the other hand... it's not that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On the other hand... it's not that I'm *not* interested in abandoned radiocomputers.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You should ask her for a hint."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should ask her for a hint.

fields.Title: Empathy: "That's why she does this."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's why she does this.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "No, definitely not. A few more prod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, definitely not. A few more producers could have come handy though -- especially when dealing with writers, some of whom routinely skipped work because of 'mental health issues' and extremely unprofessional sleep schedules...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It was impossible not to fail. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was impossible not to fail. The project was too large and no amount of money could satiate the ever-expanding ambitions of the development team.

fields.Title: You: "That sounds bad."
fields.Dialogue Text: That sounds bad.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "At the eleventh hour, the lead desi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At the eleventh hour, the lead designer, Zsiemsk-born Sulisaw Zawisza, decided that what 'Wirrl Untethered' needed was a secret mystical location at the extreme edge of the map...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Good call. It's more than the numbe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good call. It's more than the number of atoms in the observable universe.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Always read the terms of service."
fields.Dialogue Text: Always read the terms of service.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant whispers into your e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant whispers into your ear: "She repeats passwords. Programming people are all... paranoid."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""No.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good, thank you." It's not clear w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, thank you." It's not clear whether she recognizes your voice. "Please repeat, how can I help you?"

fields.Title: Mainframe: ""I didn't have a home anymore, so I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't have a home anymore, so I started keeping it in the basement, in the ice bear refrigerator (near where I went to sleep). It was perfectly safe there, the temperature conditions were *optimal*."

fields.Title: You: "Seems like a perfectly reasonable e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seems like a perfectly reasonable explanation.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The production schedule ends with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The production schedule ends with a few random notes that seem to be added sometime later.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Marked by the devil itself!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Marked by the devil itself!

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It's blank. The lower edge of the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's blank. The lower edge of the paper has been torn off.

fields.Title: You: "Press PRINT."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press PRINT.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It didn't."
fields.Dialogue Text: It didn't.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "A dusty radiocomputer sleeps on its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A dusty radiocomputer sleeps on its wired frame, forgotten and unused. Its keyboard has a rectangular ON/OFF button; a piece of paper still hangs from the printer.

fields.Title: You: "And the anomaly caused all the data..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And the anomaly caused all the data to get lost in the air?

fields.Title: You: "How many heads were there?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How many heads were there?

fields.Title: You: "What do you mean? I totally could h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What do you mean? I totally could have.

fields.Title: You: ""Do you think I should turn it on?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you think I should turn it on?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""As for me, well..." Some static. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "As for me, well..." Some static. Then... "I am sitting in my cubicle surrounded by a wall of radios."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""The filament you have inserted int..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The filament you have inserted into the reader."

fields.Title: You: "Read about capital... I want to kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read about capital... I want to know about *money*.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Like a smooth drawer, the filament..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a smooth drawer, the filament slides into place. On the keyboard, the PLAY key starts blinking.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Of course you should turn it on --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course you should turn it on -- don't you want to know what's on the filament?!

fields.Title: You: "That's pretty bad. So that's what d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's pretty bad. So that's what did them in?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Well, yeah. That, and the catastrop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well, yeah. That, and the catastrophic data loss.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It was the lead programmer's respon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was the lead programmer's responsibility to oversee weekly maintenance of the off-site copy and, well, keep it off-site. An explanatory note from the lead programmer has been attached.

fields.Title: Volition: "No, you couldn't have."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, you couldn't have.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Oh no... it was already glowing and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh no... it was already glowing and now it's also making a *sound*? It's probably some alien Seolite technology...

fields.Title: You: ""You mean that glowing thing I put..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mean that glowing thing I put inside?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Don't worry. Passwords have a way o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't worry. Passwords have a way of *turning up* sooner or later.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""'Fortress Accident SCA produces re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "'Fortress Accident SCA produces revolutionary interactive call-in radio games' -- that's what the catalogue says."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "*Ka-ching*!"
fields.Dialogue Text: *Ka-ching*!

fields.Title: Jump to: [East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good. Please repeat the password.""]
You: "Read about the workforce... Who wor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read about the workforce... Who worked there, how long?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "They thought they could bridge the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They thought they could bridge the gap with pure willpower and imagination.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "You can always do it *after* the fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can always do it *after* the fridge.

fields.Title: You: "Read the printout."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read the printout.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Behind the hatch sits a cube-like c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Behind the hatch sits a cube-like crisscross of filaments, smouldering in the dark like fireflies. Silver tape on the side says in a black marker: "THE PRODUCTION SCHEDULE".

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The paper is soaked with ink, its m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The paper is soaked with ink, its monochrome darkness spanning from margin to margin... It's not possible to make out any information.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Fortress Accident employed 18 peopl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fortress Accident employed 18 people, the bulk of the team composed of writers and concept artists. There were also radio programmers, sound engineers, a CEO, two marketing experts...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The speaker comes to life, static s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The speaker comes to life, static seeps through the machine's planar magnetic driver. An old lady greets you, her voice sounds a hundred years old...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "On the nature of the data loss, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On the nature of the data loss, there's ominously little information in the production log. It comes at the very end, where things get fuzzy and dark, where tables and numbers seem to vanish into an eerie nothingness, before their Igaunijan investor pulled the plug...

fields.Title: You: "What does it say?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What does it say?

fields.Title: You: "How many combinations could you mak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How many combinations could you make out of that?

fields.Title: Logic: "And let's face it, they didn't have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And let's face it, they didn't have any money left for a legal action.

fields.Title: You: ""Is it my birthday?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is it my birthday?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Received. I will *register* this l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Received. I will *register* this log-in attempt."

fields.Title: You: ""Let's try the password for the pro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's try the password for the production schedule."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Don't worry. Passwords have a way o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't worry. Passwords have a way of *turning up* sooner or later.

fields.Title: You: "Insert THE PRODUCTION SCHEDULE."
fields.Dialogue Text: Insert THE PRODUCTION SCHEDULE.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "...and a single overburdened produc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...and a single overburdened producer who developed a habit of popping Pyrholidon in the basement to escape his obligations.

fields.Title: You: ""What happened? It's just covered i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What happened? It's just covered in ink."

fields.Title: You: "I could have bridged the gap."
fields.Dialogue Text: I could have bridged the gap.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Even then, success remained within..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even then, success remained within an ever-narrowing margin of possibility that, despite everything, never entirely disappeared...

fields.Title: You: "Just let the numbers wash over you."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just let the numbers wash over you.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But we're looking for a fridge and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But we're looking for a fridge and we're pressed on time -- so..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Maybe the body has *stopped* decom..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe the body has *stopped* decomposing somehow..." He looks over his shoulder. "I don't know. You're in charge of this expedition, officer."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Yes. Is that the off-site copy?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Is that the off-site copy?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Received. I will *register* this l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Received. I will *register* this log-in attempt."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good, thank you." It's not clear w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, thank you." It's not clear whether she recognizes your voice. "Please repeat, is this the production schedule?"

fields.Title: You: "Is there anything else from this le..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is there anything else from this lead programmer? (Proceed.)

fields.Title: Jump to: [Mainframe: "Tiles on the cube are still smoulde..."]
Mainframe: "The first tranche of seed financing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The first tranche of seed financing brought in 150,000 rel, but then came the *delays*.

fields.Title: You: "Remove THE PRODUCTION SCHEDULE."
fields.Dialogue Text: Remove THE PRODUCTION SCHEDULE.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Lonely?" For the first time you he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lonely?" For the first time you hear her chuckle through the rustle of static. "Why would it get lonely, I get to talk to people all day."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Still no.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Still no."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good. Please repeat the password.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. Please repeat the password."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Hmm," she hums."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm," she hums.

fields.Title: You: ""It's called the production schedul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's called the production schedule."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good, I've unlocked the production..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, I've unlocked the production schedule. After ending the call, please press PRINT to access the filament."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: "Her answer is short and sharp: "No,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her answer is short and sharp: "No, that's not it."

fields.Title: You: ""Yvonne, it's me again! How are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yvonne, it's me again! How are you?"

fields.Title: You: "Read the notes at the end."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read the notes at the end.

fields.Title: You: "Tear off the printout and throw it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tear off the printout and throw it away.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Have you stirred the ghost of the D..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have you stirred the ghost of the Doomed Commercial Area from its rest? Could this be its dismembered heart, beginning to flutter?

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Thank you and good bye," the old l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you and good bye," the old lady's voice disappears along with the static.

fields.Title: Perception: "It's just black upon black, nothing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's just black upon black, nothing to see here.

fields.Title: You: "Please stop."
fields.Dialogue Text: Please stop.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""I work as a repeater at the East-I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I work as a repeater at the East-Insulindian Repeater Station. It's my job to know where you are, Fortress Accident."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Now please tell me the reason for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now please tell me the reason for your call, Fortress Accident."

fields.Title: You: ""Ah, right. Thanks for the explanat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, right. Thanks for the explanation."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Mainframe: "The first few pages give an overvie..."]
Interfacing: "She's right, actually -- nothing wr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's right, actually -- nothing wrong with keeping this type of filament memory in a fridge.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "This is where the machine's memory..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is where the machine's memory should go.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "One of them even managed to steal s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: One of them even managed to steal some valuable company property before skipping town for good.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "S. Luukanen-Kilde, the lead program..."
fields.Dialogue Text: S. Luukanen-Kilde, the lead programmer of Fortress Accident: "The off-site copy was on-site because there was no *off-site* anymore, not for me, not after eight months of crunch."

fields.Title: You: "Because of the concept artists?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Because of the concept artists?

fields.Title: You: "No, let's not go there."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, let's not go there.

fields.Title: You: "What! They lost the whole game and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What! They lost the whole game and wouldn't even pay for it?

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Something's broken. Machines aren't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something's broken. Machines aren't supposed to behave like this.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "That's not bad."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's not bad.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The first few pages give an overvie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The first few pages give an overview of the capital and workforce, while the rest of it seems to be a production schedule.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "What he means is that these things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What he means is that these things cost *money*. Why would anyone just leave it behind?

fields.Title: You: "I don't really care. (Look at the t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't really care. (Look at the table of contents again.)

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Her former colleagues would agree w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her former colleagues would agree with you.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Behind the hatch sits a cube-like c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Behind the hatch sits a cube-like crisscross of filaments, smouldering in the dark like fireflies. Silver tape on the side says in a black marker: "THE OFF-SITE COPY".

fields.Title: Mainframe: "With a quiet determination the prin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With a quiet determination the printer starts printing, a piece of paper unfolding like a hand-held fan. A black criss-cross of letters covers its surface.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "No, not the concept artists. It was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, not the concept artists. It wasn't even the writers, with their panic attacks and three-hour lunches...

fields.Title: Volition: "Not a chance."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not a chance.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good afternoon, Fortress Accident..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good afternoon, Fortress Accident on Rue de Saint-Ghislaine, this is East-Insulindian Repeater Station 1."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Now please tell me if there's anyt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now please tell me if there's anything else I can do, Fortress Accident."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Igaunija -- a god-forsaken (and tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Igaunija -- a god-forsaken (and tiny) territory in Graad that has not once, but twice wasted its independence on microfascism. The less said about Igaunija the better. Matter of fact, let's stop saying things about it right now and continue what we were doing.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It's empty like a beehive without i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's empty like a beehive without its brood. Some cables have been left dangling, disconnected...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The machine lights up like some pre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The machine lights up like some prehistoric animal stirring from its slumber, revealing virescent PLAY and PRINT keys on the keyboard. The hatch on the machine's central compartment is wide open.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Mainframe: "Tiles on the cube are still smoulde..."]
You: "Wasn't there a copy of the game, a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wasn't there a copy of the game, a *backup*?

fields.Title: You: "Uh oh."
fields.Dialogue Text: Uh oh.

fields.Title: You: "Okay, so that's what did them in?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, so that's what did them in?

fields.Title: You: "I didn't understand a word of that."
fields.Dialogue Text: I didn't understand a word of that.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A radiocomputer..." says the lieut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A radiocomputer..." says the lieutenant, watching you circle around the machine. "Just sitting here without anyone in sight." He sounds surprised and a bit cautious.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's your call." He looks over his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's your call." He looks over his shoulder, then back at the machine. "You're in charge of this expedition, officer."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""One moment..." You hear her flip t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "One moment..." You hear her flip through a catalogue, before she reads out with studious care:

fields.Title: You: ""It's called the off-site copy.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's called the off-site copy."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Maybe it's the second part of the l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe it's the second part of the leitmotiv you saw on the stained glass window.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "That's not what her colleagues thou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's not what her colleagues thought.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Tiles on the cube are still smoulde..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tiles on the cube are still smouldering, casting the framework in a soft glow. Virescent PLAY and PRINT keys shine on the keyboard.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The first few pages give an overvie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The first few pages give an overview of the capital and workforce, while the rest of it seems to be a production schedule.

fields.Title: Mainframe: ""I have compared the coordinates to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have compared the coordinates to a map of Revachol West. Turns out it's only 800 metres from here. The address is Saint-Brune 1147. I am going there to look this thing in the eye..."

fields.Title: Mainframe: "They couldn't."
fields.Dialogue Text: They couldn't.

fields.Title: You: "Keep going."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep going.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Mainframe: "Well, yeah. That, and the catastrop..."]
East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old and my name is Yvonne."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, but where are you? How did y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but where are you? How did you know where I am?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know the password.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know the password."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Unbelievable!!! Who came up with th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unbelievable!!! Who came up with those stupid passwords!

fields.Title: You: "Wait, why did a *radio game* need s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, why did a *radio game* need so many artists?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is where the memory should go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is where the memory should go," the lieutenant notes, observing the machine.

fields.Title: You: ""Why did you call me Fortress Accid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why did you call me Fortress Accident?"

fields.Title: You: ""And what's that -- this 'interacti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And what's that -- this 'interactive call-in radio game'?"

fields.Title: Mainframe: "In its short time of existence, For..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In its short time of existence, Fortress Accident SCA managed to burn through truly *insane* amounts of money.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: "The static drowns her response. "An..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The static drowns her response. "Any other questions?" you hear her ask when the connection finally improves.

fields.Title: You: "Right, what happened?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Right, what happened?

fields.Title: You: "Yeah, how bad could it be?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, how bad could it be?

fields.Title: You: "What have I done?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What have I done?

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old and my name is Yvonne. Now please repeat, is this the production schedule?"

fields.Title: You: ""What's the production schedule?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's the production schedule?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""That was a question. Have you inse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That was a question. Have you inserted it into the core?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good. Please repeat the password.""]
East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good, I've unlocked the off-site c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, I've unlocked the off-site copy. After ending the call, please press PRINT to access the filament."

fields.Title: You: "Say: "After death -- life again.""
fields.Dialogue Text: Say: "After death -- life again."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I am alive. I am 74 years old and my name is Yvonne. Now please repeat, is this the off-site copy?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Good, thank you." It's not clear w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, thank you." It's not clear whether she recognizes your voice. "Please repeat, is this the off-site copy?"

fields.Title: You: "Skim through the production schedul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Skim through the production schedule, whatever it is.

fields.Title: You: "Insert THE OFF-SITE COPY."
fields.Dialogue Text: Insert THE OFF-SITE COPY.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Please repeat -- is this the produ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please repeat -- is this the production schedule?"

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The filament slides out of its glow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The filament slides out of its glowing nest.

fields.Title: You: "Examine the printout again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the printout again.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Odd." The lieutenant runs his hand..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Odd." The lieutenant runs his hand over the ink-soaked paper, staining his fingertips. "Something is obviously broken here."

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Nothing happens."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing happens.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "No. Even then success remained with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. Even then success remained within an ever-narrowing margin of possibility that, despite everything, never entirely disappeared...

fields.Title: You: "The what now?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The what now?

fields.Title: Mainframe: "No, it was good. Too good."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it was good. Too good.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Do you really want to know? There s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do you really want to know? There seems to be a calculation here, but it may take a while...

fields.Title: You: "Keep going."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep going.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "He's dying for a cigarette. Come to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's dying for a cigarette. Come to think of it, you are, too.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""They're merely cautious," says the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They're merely cautious," says the old lady. "It's my job to protect their filaments as a password repeater at the East-Insulindian Station."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Fortress Accident, is there anythi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fortress Accident, is there anything else I can do for you today?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What, you're just going to guess?"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, you're just going to guess?" The lieutenant shakes his head, staring at the glowing radiocomputer. Seems like the repeater station hasn't heard his words however, for the line is still silent.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm afraid we're not doing that. U..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm afraid we're not doing that. Unless we want to wait for a month."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Fortress Accident is the company o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fortress Accident is the company on whose name the terminal you're currently using has been registered to."

fields.Title: You: ""Wow. So conceptual.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow. So conceptual."

fields.Title: Half Light: "What does she mean *that's not it*?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What does she mean *that's not it*?! What's the password then???

fields.Title: You: ""I might have a password for the of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I might have a password for the off-site copy."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Looks like gibberish. Better get ru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like gibberish. Better get running again.

fields.Title: You: "Remove THE OFF-SITE COPY."
fields.Dialogue Text: Remove THE OFF-SITE COPY.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It's a project report written by th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's a project report written by the lead producer Andrew 'Andy' Schott about 'Wirrl Untethered', a radio game developed by studio Fortress Accident.

fields.Title: Perception: "A single speck of white shines out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A single speck of white shines out from the shade -- for some reason the printer decided to spare this one tiny dot of paper.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "The team spent weeks on the phone w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The team spent weeks on the phone with Lintel, the service provider, but despite their diagnostics they could never produce a satisfactory explanation or pay for the loss.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Mysteriously enough, it seems that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Mysteriously enough, it seems that the off-site copy happened to be *on-site* when the catastrophic data loss occurred...

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Something spooky happened with the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something spooky happened with the machines and the game was lost.

fields.Title: You: ""Yvonne, my partner tells me that y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yvonne, my partner tells me that you're here because radiocomputer guys are all paranoid."

fields.Title: You: ""This is the police. Please open th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the police. Please open this thing."

fields.Title: You: ""I swear I haven't touched anything!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I swear I haven't touched anything!"

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Now, can you please repeat the pas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now, can you please repeat the password?" the voice in the machine asks again. She sounds cold in the damp air.

fields.Title: You: ""What's the off-site copy?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's the off-site copy?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Really? She just used the same pas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Really? She just used the same password?" The lieutenant seems almost disappointed to discover that, as he murmurs:  "Maybe those radiocomputer guys aren't that paranoid after all..."

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Eventually the damage reached 400,0..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Eventually the damage reached 400,000 rel with only half of the game finished.

fields.Title: You: "Press PLAY again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press PLAY again.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Four-hundred thousand rel?! Jommai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Four-hundred thousand rel?! Jommaijoo, these guys knew how to party!

fields.Title: You: "Turn on the machine."
fields.Dialogue Text: Turn on the machine.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Like a smooth drawer, the filament..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a smooth drawer, the filament slides into place. On the keyboard, the PLAY key starts blinking.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the table of contents."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the table of contents.

fields.Title: You: "Press PLAY."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press PLAY.

fields.Title: You: "Oh, so they were done in by their o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, so they were done in by their own ambition.

fields.Title: Mainframe: ""Still haven't gotten an answer fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Still haven't gotten an answer from Lintel about what happened. All I could get were the physical coordinates of the error on the East-Insulindian front on that day. Since the computation happened on-air, I reckoned it had to coincide with an actually existing location..."

fields.Title: Mainframe: "So many. At last count there were a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So many. At last count there were approximately 10,000 heads for 10,000 headless men, all of which could be endlessly recombined.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "That is, until they discovered the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That is, until they discovered the Valley of the Heads.

fields.Title: You: "This is some insane shit. Who were..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is some insane shit. Who were these people?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant taps his foot impati..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant taps his foot impatiently, his arms folded tight against his chest.

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""Open the hatch on the compartment...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Open the hatch on the compartment. Don't touch the wires, a current is running through it, but the core is safe. There's a filament inside -- I need to know what it's called."

fields.Title: You: "Say: "After life -- death.""
fields.Dialogue Text: Say: "After life -- death."

fields.Title: You: ""A password? I'm really bad at pass..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A password? I'm really bad at passwords. Can you give me a hint?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Really? She just used the same pas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Really? She just used the same password?" The lieutenant seems almost disappointed to discover that.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "Nothing happens."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing happens.

fields.Title: You: ""That's all for now." (Press OFF/SI..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all for now." (Press OFF/SILENT.)

fields.Title: Logic: "Why did Fortress Accident have so m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why did Fortress Accident have so many concept artists?

fields.Title: Jump to: [Mainframe: "Tiles on the cube are still smoulde..."]
Mainframe: "The world had never seen their kind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The world had never seen their kind before and might never again.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "What if you broke the radiocomputer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if you broke the radiocomputer? What if it's never going to stop?!

fields.Title: You: ""What are you, a *machine*? Or are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you, a *machine*? Or are you *alive*?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: "The old lady sighs, as a wave of st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The old lady sighs, as a wave of static distorts her voice to a robotic sprawl. "If you are unsure, could you please take a look?"

fields.Title: East-Insulindian Repeater Station: ""No, that's not it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, that's not it."

fields.Title: Mainframe: "They tried to make a 4,000,000 rel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They tried to make a 4,000,000 rel game with 400,000 in their bank account.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "A hint system is not part of the pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A hint system is not part of the protocol for repeater stations.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "It sounds like something cracks, be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It sounds like something cracks, before the piece of paper starts filling up with pure black ink.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The filaments you have would fit pe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The filaments you have would fit perfectly inside the compartment.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "A bar of fabric right above the key..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A bar of fabric right above the keyboard starts producing a soft hum. The sound of static seeps through the machine's planar magnetic driver.

fields.Title: Mainframe: "When the project was returned, it w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: When the project was returned, it was completely blank.
